In this statement, the President expresses his condolences to the families of those who lost their lives in the tornadoes and severe weather that hit Joplin, Missouri and other communities in the Midwest. He praises the heroic efforts of those who are responding to the disaster and helping their friends and neighbors. The President mentions that FEMA is working with state and local officials to support response and recovery efforts, and assures that the federal government is ready to assist as needed.